main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were reported in San Diego, California, during December 1966.
interesting points: The objects had red and green lights and were observed for approximately nine minutes,The reports included sightings from various individuals including military personnel and a local engineer,One witness described the objects as brilliant orange in color and flickering while dropping flaming material,The conclusion of the investigation deemed the sightings to be a hoax connected to debris,There was no photograph present in the reports.
witness description: military personnel and a senior mechanical engineer
